        <h1>About</h1>
        <p>
            In Sweden, the average amount of Co2 emissions per person is 4,2 tons per year. About a third of the emissions comes from various means of transportation. The effects of Co2 emissions are known to most people, but do we sometimes fail acknowledge the extent of our own personal impact on the environment? <br /><br />

            On this website you can translate your travels into the number of trees needed to compensate for the carbon footprint made by your trip. You can choose between various means of transportation and you can save your travels to your account where you also have a tree count, which illustrates the total amount of trees you hypothetically "owe" the world.

            <br /><br />The tree count is merely a way to illustrate the carbon footprint caused by your choice of transportation, not the solution to the environmental crisis. If you would really like to compensate for your Co2 footprints we reccomend emissions trading, where you buy permits to emitt a certain amout of Co2, and by doing so you decrease the amount of permits available for purchase.

